Which camera store did you go to?  Your rant may be fully justified,
but without knowing where you went it does no one any good.

As to your general statement about camera stores ripping you off - you
couldn't be more wrong.  I've been a serious amateur photography for
over 40 years.  Camera stores are, in general, staffed with the most
knowledgeable and honest sales people of any specialty field.  You'll
get a lot more than a receipt when you buy something from them rather
than at a big box discount store.  So, it just comes down to what you
want for your money.

And finally, low end electronics, and this includes digital cameras,
is throw away technology.  They're just not worth fixing.  And any
digital camera that can be replaced brand new for under $150.00 is
definitely low end.

Regards,
